RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 1 1/16M Turf CR: 62. Maiden Special Weight Purse 38500. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS SIRED BY REGISTERED INDIANA STALLIONS MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile and 1/16 on the main track.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIZZY JUSTICE saved ground while unhurried down the backstretch, moved up through the turn, cut the corner into the lane, was in a bit tight when straightening, cleared near the sixteenth pole and was kept to the task to last. REDHOTJUSTICE was last away and trailed into the first turn, was unhurried into the far turn, continued near the rail through the turn, angled sharply into the lane and into the four path, straightened and was closing in. THIZZLE set the pace along the inside into the lane, was challenged by the winner near the eighth pole, bumped with that one near the sixteenth pole and gave ground grudgingly. SHANGHAI EXPRESS stalked the pace from the two path through the far turn then weakened in the drive. BEYOND JUSTICE was in the two path through the turns when never far back then lacked a closing response. MEAN ELENITA was bothered into the first turn, raced in the two path through the far turn, came into the lane from the six path and never was a factor. NOW HERES THE PLAN chased the pace from the three path into the far turn, was asked for more in mid-turn and tired through the lane. GOODY FOUR SHOES came out into the first turn bothering rival, trailed into the lane and was outrun. SEQUEEKER was in the three path through the far turn when near the back, came into the lane from the six path and was never in it. TAMARAC LADY raced three wide into the firs turn, raced in the four path through the far turn and was empty into the lane.
